opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 22nd day of July, 2015, as the challenged order is not a final one, the Petition for Allowance of Appeal is DISMISSED. See 42 Pa.C.S. § 724(a) (stating that only final orders of the Commonwealth Court, sitting in its appellate jurisdiction, may be challenged through allocatur review).
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.
